com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message

Class HttpBaseMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpBaseMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.intel.icecp.core.Message, OnCommandMessage<HttpBridge_Module>, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HttpDataMessage, HttpSetupMessage, HttpTeardownMessage

    public abstract class HttpBaseMessage
extends Object
implements com.intel.icecp.core.Message, OnCommandMessage<HttpBridge_Module>
    Base message for http_bridge module messages. This base class contains the static constants used by the extended classes, and the common fields used by all commands.

    returnCmdChannelURI = The user specified channel where the command status is returned.

    connectionId = the unique id for the connection. Returned from the Setup command.

    status = the HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS of the command.

    The JsonTypeInfo annotation allows the deserialization to work for the correct extended classes. If you remove this, the deserialization will not work.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • HTTP_CMD_CHANNEL_NAME

        public static final String HTTP_CMD_CHANNEL_NAME
        The well known command channel for this module. The module is subscribed to this channel name and receives the commands. Publish all commands to this channel.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • cmdReturnChannelURI

        public URI cmdReturnChannelURI
        The return channel for all commmands. Specify the channel name that you want return status to be sent. This channel should be unique for your usage.

      • connectionId

        public long connectionId
        When a setup command is sent to the module, it will create a connectionId and return it on the return channel. This connectionId needs to be specified for all subsequent commands (eg, data messages HttpDataMessage and teardown messages HttpTeardownMessage

      • status

        public HttpBaseMessage.HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS status
        The status of the command. This value is set and returned for each command on the return channel. See HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS values for more info.
